#. .
#. The original English version uses the following abbreviated forms:
#. .
#. * Tr    = Trunk
#. * Br    = Branch
#. * Jnc   = Junction
#. * Co    = Core
#. * Le    = Leaf
#. * Rt    = Root
#. * Aux   = Auxiliary
#. * Lo    = Lower
#. * Up    = Upper
#. * Prt   = Port
#. * Ln    = Line
#. * Par   = Parallel
#. .
#. Because of issues with randomization (?), `number` and `upalpha` actually produce placeholders filled in
#. through a later step using Lua instead. Anywhere in the generated name where a `@` is found, an uppercase
#. Latin letter (English only) is substituted, while `%` is substituted with a Roman numeral (0-9).
